item.title: Commands.java
item.dc:creator: @doom_j doom_j
item.description:
@doom_j wrote:

If you created a new file, you need to add the path of that file to your compiler

like: com.server.world.packet.commands.hello

If you just had commands and not hello, then the files in the hello folder wouldn’t be compiled.

Read full topic

item.title: Commands.java
item.dc:creator: @doom_j doom_j
item.description:
@doom_j wrote:

Make sure the path where you command is located is added into the path in the compiler, that is one of the problems with packaged servers, you have to define the path of a new folder in the compiler or else all the code in the folder is skipped.
